The paper addresses the problem of finding the shortest path in an unknown physical environment, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm presented involves decision-making and control, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses variations and evaluations of the algorithm, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) as they involve optimization and analysis of data.
